  "prompt": "What is the best way to withdraw money from freelancer.com in indian currency?",
  "response": "Withdrawing money from **Freelancer.com** to an Indian bank account requires a few steps. Here\u2019s the best way to withdraw funds in **Indian Rupees (INR)**:\n\n---\n\n### **Steps to Withdraw Money from Freelancer.com in INR:**\n\n1. **Complete Verification (If Not Done Already)**  \n   - Ensure your **Freelancer.com** account is fully verified. This includes:\n     - Identity verification (uploading a government-issued ID like Aadhaar or PAN card).\n     - Bank account verification (providing accurate bank details).\n\n2. **Link Your Indian Bank Account**  \n   - Go to **Payments** > **Withdraw Funds** on your Freelancer.com dashboard.\n   - Select the **Bank Transfer** option.\n   - Enter your bank details, including:\n     - **Account Holder Name** (must match your Freelancer account name).\n     - **Bank Name**.\n     - **Account Number**.\n     - **IFSC Code**.\n\n3. **Check Withdrawal Options**  \n   - Freelancer.com offers multiple withdrawal methods, but **Bank Transfer** is the most straightforward for INR.\n   - Ensure your withdrawal currency is set to **INR**.\n\n4. **Withdrawal Fees**  \n   - Freelancer.com charges a **withdrawal fee** (check their updated fees on the platform).\n   - Additionally, your bank may charge a small **foreign transaction fee** or **currency conversion fee**.\n\n5. **Minimum Withdrawal Amount**  \n   - Ensure your account balance meets the **minimum withdrawal limit** (usually around $30 or equivalent in INR).\n\n6. **Initiate the Withdrawal**  \n   - Select the amount you wish to withdraw and confirm the transaction.\n   - The funds will be converted to INR and transferred to your bank account.\n\n7. **Processing Time**  \n   - Bank transfers typically take **3 to 7 business days** to reflect in your Indian bank account.\n\n---\n\n### **Tips for Smooth Withdrawals:**\n- Use a **zero-balance savings account** to avoid unnecessary charges.\n- Double-check your bank details to prevent delays or errors.\n- Keep your account verified and updated to avoid issues with withdrawals.\n\n---\n\n### **Alternative Methods (if needed):**\n- **Skrill**: You can withdraw funds to Skrill and then transfer them to your Indian bank account. However, Skrill charges fees for withdrawals and currency conversion.\n- **PayPal**: Freelancer.com no longer supports PayPal withdrawals directly, so this option is not available.\n\n---\n\nBy following these steps, you can efficiently withdraw your earnings from **Freelancer.com** in **Indian Rupees**. Always check the platform for the latest policies and fees to ensure a smooth process.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
